" --- VIM BASIC CONFIG FOR RUST ---

" 1. Enable Syntax Highlighting (The Colors!)
syntax on
filetype plugin indent on

" 2. Line Numbers (Critical for finding errors)
set number

" 3. Indentation (Rust standard is 4 spaces, not tabs)
set tabstop=4       " Show existing tabs as 4 spaces width
set shiftwidth=4    " When indenting with '>', use 4 spaces
set expandtab       " On pressing tab, insert 4 spaces

" 4. Search Settings
set hlsearch        " Highlight all search results
set incsearch       " Jump to the first match while typing

" 5. Visual Aids
set ruler           " Show line and column number in bottom right
set cursorline      " Highlight the current line you are editing

" 6. Color Scheme
" 'desert' or 'slate' are great built-in themes for terminals
colorscheme desert
